title: Figure 3.4: A Comparative Summary of Governance Theories
---
| Governance Model | Core Unit of Analysis | Primary Goal | Major Weakness/Critique |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Weberian (Centralized)** | Central Bureaucracy / Hierarchy | Rational Efficiency & National Uniformity | Rigidity, Information Loss, Low Responsiveness to Local Needs |
| **Public Choice (Market-based)** | Consumer-Voter / Fragmented Jurisdiction | Allocative Efficiency & Preference Matching | Ignores Equity, Assumes Mobility/Information, Risk of Soft Budget Constraints |
| **Polycentric (New Institutionalism)** | Local Institution / Self-Governing Unit | Institutional Resilience & Endogenous Capacity | Risk of Local Elite Capture, High Transaction Costs, Coordination Complexity |
